Illicit alcohol is w being sold in thermos flasks disguised as tea within markets and other public areas in Eldoret. Uasin Gishu County Commissioner Abdi Hassan yesterday said street children are being used to supply drugs and sell illicit alcohol in thermos flasks usually used for tea. Hassan says they have ordered the clearing of bushes around Sosiani River used as hiding places for street families who engage in drugs, alcoholism and crime. More than 80 people had been arrested and charged in courts within two weeks over the sale and distribution of alcohol and also other crimes.